parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause slow acceleration, jerky movements, and improper shifting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The transmission slipping and jerking can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the transmission.
symptoms: loud thumping noise underneath the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Transmission Interaction Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interaction issue between the brake pedal and transmission can cause improper shifting, loss of acceleration, and accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle feels as if the transmission has improperly shifted when the brake pedal is depressed and the turning signals are activated

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag warning indicator illumination can distract the driver, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: loud thumping noise underneath the vehicle when in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of power steering, brake lights, and other essential systems, increasing the risk of accidents and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly dies while in drive
the check engine light is on but no code is reading properly
loss of electric power to the touch screen display
and hesitation or failure to start the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Vehicle Dynamic Control (VDC) system can cause the vehicle to fail to slow or stop, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle does not stop or slow when the brakes are depressed
a rattling noise is heard in the front of the car
the VDC system engages and the flashing icon appears
and the vehicle pulls sharply to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to struggle to accelerate, change gears, and move, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud noise when shifting from park into drive or reverse
jerking or hesitation when taking off from a stop
weird loud noise coming from the transmission
and trouble gaining speed when entering a highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to lose the ability to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
A defective battery can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: Battery failure despite being only one year old.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: Fuel gauge reads incorrectly when the car is filled up with gas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Traction control light comes on and off for no reason
